@gaul I have to say it but I guess this completely breaks OSGi compatibility. I introduced the bnd plugin here which really simplified the OSGi support https://github.com/apache/jclouds/commit/8ac994c2b5d509ca2877efdd77c35881d58ac3e3 . Please revert the commit and I will take a look.

Probably related
https://github.com/apache/jclouds/pull/176#issuecomment-1622407203

I attempted to apply a JIRA account a few days ago, but haven't received a response yet. It would be greatly appreciated if you could help me record this issue!

I'm trying to fix the bug, but the codes about blob/payload/stream are too complex for me, and it looks like you have some TODOs and ongoing PRs on it. I am not able to fix the problem. What I can do is just to revert the following snippet and wait for your help.
```java
         InputStream is = blob.getPayload().openStream();
         if (is instanceof FileInputStream) {
            // except for FileInputStream since large MPU can open too many fds
            is.close();
            payload = blob.getPayload();
         } else {
            blob.resetPayload(/*release=*/ false);
            payload = new InputStreamPayload(is);
         }
```
